Osmond May Install Fairey to Run Lloyds Branches, Telegraph Says

-- B y   F i r a t   K a y a k i r a n
-- 
2011-08-07T07:28:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-07/osmond-may-install-fairey-to-run-lloyds-branches-telegraph-says.html
Michael Fairey, chairman of Horizon
Acquisition Company Plc, may run  Lloyds Banking Group Plc (LLOY) ’s 632
branches should Hugh Osmond win a bidding process, the Sunday
Telegraph reported without saying where it got the information.  Entrepreneur Osmond, who is bidding for Lloyd’s branches
through his equity firm Sun Capital, lined up Fairey, former
deputy chief executive officer of Lloyds TSB for 10 years until
2008, to head the new bank, the newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Firat Kayakiran in London at 
 fkayakiran@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
